festival.introText:
Parked Out is the brainchild of Sleepin Is Cheatin and Wired Events - this annual festival brings the 2 giants of the nightlife industry together, using all their expertise to create a truly mind-blowing day of dance music, madness and mayhem. 

Set at the idyllic Old Post Office site which is perfectly situated in close distance to Barnsley, Sheffield, Rotherham, Huddersfield and Leeds. 

The site boasts 3 acres of car parks, an actual park, inflatable arenas & domes, the pub itself and lots of grassy areas to give it that real festival feel. All the arenas are fully under cover, no risk of the typical English weather spoiling the fun.

Parked Out returns to the Old Post Office grounds on Saturday 28th May, with what has been dubbed the biggest line up & largest site layout ever.

------------------------------------------------

PARKED OUT RETURNS IN 2022!

Back on our usual weekend, SATURDAY 28TH MAY!

Last weekend was amazing, our biggest PARKED OUT to date!

Expect it to be even BIGGER & CRAZIER next year with what we have in store!

As always - a HUGE DJ line up across multiple arenas! Fairground rides, production levels like never before & much more!

THANK YOU EVERYONE FOR MAKING THIS YEAR'S EVENT AN UNFORGETTABLE ONE!?

We’ll see you all again in 2022??

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Does Parked Out Festival have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, Parked Out is a non camping festival so camping equipment is not needed.

faqs.question: How much are Parked Out tickets?
faqs.answer: Head to the tickets section above for the latest prices.

faqs.question: Where is Parked Out Festival?
faqs.answer: Parked Out Festival is located at The Old Post Office in Barnsley. The address is: Huddersfield Road, Barnsley, S75 4DE

faqs.question: Are pre-payment plan tickets available?
faqs.answer: Payment Plan tickets are not currently available for this event.

faqs.question: Does Parked Out have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes you must be 18 or over to attend Parked Out. You may be asked to show photo ID.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Parked Out Festival?
faqs.answer: You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into Parked Out 2022. There will be a wide variety of food and drink stalls inside the festival.

faqs.question: Is there parking at Parked Out?
faqs.answer: Strictly NO on site parking is available
